    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to
                                Senhor <persName type="to">Mendonça</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At your interview with me yesterday you
                            communicated copy of a telegraphic instruction you had received from the
                            minister for foreign affairs, directing you to ask if the Government of
                            the United States would authorize its minister at Lisbon to protect
                            Brazilian citizens during the suspension of diplomatic relations with
                            Portugal.</p>
                <p>Having taken the President’s directions in this regard, I have the
                            pleasure to inform you that the minister, of the United States at Lisbon
                            will be instructed, by cable, to use his friendly offices, with the
                            acquiescence of the Portuguese Government, for the protection of
                            Brazilian citizens in Portugal or the Portuguese dependencies during the
                            present suspension of diplomatic relations between those countries.</p>
                <p>Promising myself the further pleasure of communicating to you such reply
                            as I may receive from Mr. Caruth,</p>
                <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
